41073,variable,FRBACKPACKSLIM,,FR Backpack Slim,1,0,visible,Perfect to carry your skates and everything you need for your daily life!,"FR Backpack Slim
\n<span lang=""en-us"">The latest generation of the FR Slim Backpack is available in Black, Blue, or Grey.
\n<span lang=""en-us"">Built with carefully selected materials, stitching, and zippers to ensure optimal durability.
\nIt features a main pocket with a computer compartment, 2 zipper pockets on the outer layer, open pockets on both sides for easy access, and a rain cover.
\nThe FR Slim Backpack is specifically designed to carry a pair of skates inserted between the main pocket and the outer layer, secured by 6 buckles for optimal attachment.

\nExtremely practical, the FR Slim Backpack is the ideal skating accessory: compact enough to stay out of the way while skating, yet spacious enough to carry everything you need for a weekend getaway.

Jackson VIP Rink Skate:
The Jackson skate company has been a global leader in the figure skating industry for the past 20 years.

A few years ago the Jackson decided to get involved in the Roller Derby world by introducing the Elite, Competitor, and Vantage leather boots.

The Jackson joint venture with Atom alias Luigino skate to put together some exciting derby skate and recreational quad skates.

The Jackson VIP outdoor skate is perfect for fitness skaters and beginners.
The New Vantage boot has a high-quality Microfiber with an exceptional fit.
The VIP Rink Roller skate features:

Powerslide is proud to release the Next Mery Munoz Pro 80\, they were inspired by the legendary Next Core 80 inline skates\, which are among the best hard boot urban freeride skates on the market!

Thanks to the TRINITY 3-point mounting the performance of Next skates swept aside the competitors.

The heat-moldable MYFIT Recall Dual Fit liner with its memory fit Padding provides this little bit of extra comfort that makes you feel great from the very first stride and wants to let you skate longer with more pleasure.

",,,taxable,,1,,,0,0,0.65,7,7.0,6.0,0,,,,"Inline Speed Skates > Inline Skate Wheels > Bont Inline Skate Wheels, Inline Speed Skates > Inline Skate Bont > Bont Wheels, Inline Speed Skates > Inline Skate Wheels, Inline Speed Skates",,,"http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/redmagichardcore125mmfirmredshield_1024x1024.jpeg, http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/RedMagicHardCore125mmXFirmredshield_1024x1024.jpeg",,,,,BontWheelsInlineRedMagic125,,,,0,Bont,,,ExtraField 1,Bont Red Magic Hardcore 125 Speed Wheels,1.0,0.0,ExtraField 6,"
Bont Red Magic Hardcore 125mm Inline Speed Wheels

The Red Magic Hardcore is the first 125mm professional inline speed skating racing wheel to use an aluminum hub. 125mm wheels are a lot larger than 110mm wheels so there is a lot more flex that needs to be controlled\, the best way to control this flex is by upgrading the hub from plastic to aluminum. The 125mm Red Magic Hardcore inline skate wheel has been an instant hit\, winning the first race of the season in Berlin and it has won most of the inline world championships marathons since its release. 

The wheel has a full 24mm width\, unlike some competitors that have opted for 20-22mm wheels. Version 2.0 now has a perfect bearing seat. 

125mm wheels are the fastest wheel size and the Red Magic Hardcore is the fastest 125mm wheel in the world. This wheel is a dual-durometer wheel which means it has two layers of urethane. 

The inner band is made of an extremely high rebounding super ball type of material and the other urethane is very very fast. What makes this wheel stand out from the competition is its amazing cornering grip. There is no other wheel like it. In addition\, this wheel has amazing wet weather capabilities. Unless it is an all-out storm\, this wheel is very capable in damp skating conditions. If you want the fastest 125mm inline wheel on the market\, you have found it. 

The urethane is poured by MPC and it uses their patented high rebound flex band.

Hydrogen Pro 125MM XXFirm Inline Speed Wheels

The Hydrogen Pro incorporates a multi-layer technology\, Mtech®\, which is comprised of two layers of urethane to provide the ultimate footprint for grip\, rebound for speed/energy return\, roll\, and wear. This combined with the core makes it the most responsive wheel you can put on your skates. 

Hydrogen Pro 125mm XX-Firm wheels are designed for marathons and open road races by providing optimal performance. Made in the USA with an exclusive dual-pour urethane formula\, the outer ring enhances wear while the inner ring improves mechanical grip. XX-Firm delivers the highest durability\, grips extremely well on smoother surfaces\, has a high level of stability\, and is optimum straight-line speed.

Their elite performance provided advanced speed with excellent wear and efficiency\, these wheels can be skated in all conditions and supply the most roll of all the hardnesses. 

The inner ring is softer for flex and the outer ring is firmer for speed. The turbine core helps keep the straight-line speed with vibration absorption and control. 

These wheels will give you long-lasting performance!

6 wheels per set

Hydrogen Pro 90MM XFirm Inline Speed Wheels,"
Features
Hydrogen Pro 90MM XFirm Inline Speed Wheels

The Hydrogen Pro incorporates a multi-layer technology, Mtech®, which is comprised of two layers of urethane to provide the ultimate footprint for grip, rebound for speed/energy return, roll, and wear. This combined with the core makes it the most responsive wheel you can put on your skates.

Hydrogen Pro 90MM X-Firm wheels are designed for marathons and open road races by providing optimal performance. Made in the USA with an exclusive dual-pour urethane formula, the outer ring enhances wear while the inner ring improves mechanical grip. X-Firm provides consistent speed, a high level of stability, and great in all race conditions for allround performance and versatility on track and road.
Their elite performance provided advanced speed with excellent wear and efficiency, these wheels can be skated in all conditions, but works better on smooth surfaces, hard and dry.
The inner ring is softer for flex and the outer ring is firmer for speed. The turbine core helps keep the straight-line speed with vibration absorption and control.
These wheels will give you long-lasting performance!

8 wheels per set
","
Technical Specification
Roll Firm: when race conditions are rough or slick
Roll X-Firm: when race conditions are hard, smooth, and dry

Roll XX-Firm: when race conditions are perfect hard, smooth and fast.

42206,variable,PowerslideHCEvoPro110Trinity,,Powerslide HC Evo Pro 110 Freestyle Skate,1,0,visible,"Powerslide HC Eco pro 110, iconic carbon skate for exciting urban skating sessions. Fast and agile setup for endless fun.
\nCode: 908449","Unleash Your Skating Prowess with the Powerslide HC Evo 110

\nLooking to push your skating performance to a whole new level? Look no further than the Powerslide HC Evo 110 Carbon inline skate - it’s the epitome of speed, agility, and performance. Engineered with cutting-edge features, this high-performance inline skate is designed to elevate your skills and take you to new heights. Crafted with a strong, lightweight and durable carbon shell, the HC Evo 110 Carbon offers the perfect balance of strength, stability, and flexibility. Experience enhanced power transfer with every stride, allowing you to roll effortlessly.

\nSpecifically designed to incorporate the famous TRINITY 3-point mounting system, this skate provides unrivalled stability and control. The innovative design delivers optimal energy transfer, allowing you to make quick turns and maneuvers with precision. Connecting to the boot with three connection points, the TRINITY system creates a channel that brings your wheels as close to the foot as possible, further improving stability and control. The Nova 260mm/3x110mm frame makes the most of the three-wheel setup. The 260mm frame length and large wheel size provide a smooth and responsive ride every time while maintaining control and maneuverability, even at high speeds.

\nPrepare to conquer virtually any surface- from asphalt to cement, to track, and everything in between with the Undercover Raw White 85A wheels. These high-performance wheels provide excellent grip and durability, and with an improved TPU core, your ride will be exceptionally smooth.

\nTo ensure a smooth, fast-rolling skating experience, the Powerslide HC Evo 110 Carbon comes fitted with high-precision WICKED ABEC 9 chrome steel bearings. These superior bearings are designed to reduce friction while delivering maximum speed that will leave you feeling unstoppable.

\nDon't miss your chance to experience the pinnacle of skating excellence. Upgrade to the Powerslide HC Evo 110 Carbon today and discover a whole new level of inline skating performance. Unleash your potential, push your limits, and embrace the thrill of speed like never before. Your skating journey begins with the HC Evo 110 Carbon.
\nAll Powerslide Urban skates are coming
\nfrom Europe if the size is not in our store,
\nyou could expect 10 to 15 days for us to have
\nthem ready to ship. We will let you know immediately
\nafter you place the order.

\ncode: 908449",,,taxable,,0,,,0,0,11.0,19,18.0,7.0,0,,,,"Inline Speed Skates > Inline Skate Powerslide > Powerslide Urban Freestyle Skate, Freestyle-Urban Skates > Powerslide Urban Skates",,,"http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/POWERSLIDE-HC-Evo-Pro-110-scaled.jpg, http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/POWERSLIDE-HC-Evo-Pro-110-2-scaled.jpg, http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/POWERSLIDE-HC-Evo-Pro-110-3-scaled.jpg, http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/POWERSLIDE-HC-Evo-Pro-110-4-scaled.jpg, http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/POWERSLIDE-HC-Evo-Pro-110-5-scaled.jpg",,,,,PowerslideHCEvoPro110Trinity,,,,0,Powerslide,,,ExtraField 1,Powerslide HC Evo Pro 90 Trinity Freeskate,1.0,0.0,ExtraField 6,"

Powerslide HC EVO Pro 90Trinity skate

Powerslide HC Evo 110 - The pinnacle of freestyle skating

The Powerslide HC Evo 110 is loved for its great performance and comfort right out of the box.
This is the third generation coming with a new look based on a mix of nylon mesh and PU-leather including
a TPU panel for extra lateral support.

The patented TRINITY mounting boosts your performance to another level thanks to the incredible power transfer
and reactivity\, the perfect control and balance as well as the outstanding vibration control.
The 3-wheel rocker setup based on the Nexus frame\, was especially designed for freestyle skating.

Bigger wheels make sitting tricks like the 'Christie' easier.
Furthermore they give your ankles more leverage\, allowing you to lift your heel and toe higher.
It's easier to balance on one wheel with more speed and now with the introduction of bigger wheels
it makes speed maintenance and balance easier than ever.

You can even rocker your left and right skates differently if you prefer.

The skate is powered by Powerslide Spinner wheels and Wicked ABEC 9 fresspin bearings.

The HC Evo Pro is featuring a built in 3mm higher heel raise to give you a little bit of extra forward lean.

The heat-moldable shell allows you to adjust the fit time and time again if needed.

Over time the HC Evo Pro is a lightweight allround carbon skate which doesn't just has made up its name
in freestyle skating but also in other disciplines like freeride\, downhill or simply fitness skating.

42229,simple,JunkJujuHiloFrame3X110,,Junk Juju Hilo Frame 3X110 - 1X100MM,1,0,visible,"The Juju frames by Junk, brings you some good Juju for ultimate performance. ","
Junk Juju Hilo Frame 3X110 - 1X100MM

The Juju frames by Junk, brings you some good Juju for ultimate performance. Engineered for speed, these frames are the lightest Junk creation. Influenced and tested by world champions and top-line speed skaters.

Like all Junk frames, there are built using a single piece of Aircraft Aluminum 7075-T6. Processed using CNC machinery, which is a manufacturing process in which a computer is programmed to grind the piece into a specific shape. This process ensures the quality of each frame making it precise and symmetrical. T6 heat treatment was applied to increase stiffness to an optical level of stability, control, and responsiveness for each frame. Thanks to its geometry this Juju frame also features sleek groves meant to reduce weight and coincidentally add to its stunning design.

They’re the lightest Junk frames model and have the lowest center of gravity. Juju is built for agility and lightness for both short sprints and grueling long races.

42305,simple,RollLineAccSkateRollinTrolley,,ROLL-LINE Skate Rolling Trolley,1,0,visible,"

ROLL-LINE Skate Rolling Trolley

\nThe Roll-Line Skate Rolling Trolley is the perfect solution for skaters looking to transport their gear with ease. This trolley is designed to hold one pair of roller skates along with numerous accessories, ensuring that you have everything you need for a great skating session. Lightweight and spacious, it provides ample storage without adding unnecessary weight, making it ideal for both everyday use and travel.

\nWith dimensions of 22"" (59cm) tall, 13.5"" (34.5cm) wide, and 9"" (23cm) deep, this bag is compact enough to fit as cabin luggage on most airlines. This makes it a convenient choice for skaters who travel frequently for competitions or training. The trolley features a sturdy handle and smooth-rolling wheels, ensuring effortless mobility. The durable construction and high-quality materials guarantee that your equipment remains protected and secure.

\nWhether you're heading to the rink or traveling across the country, the Roll-Line Skate Rolling Trolley is a reliable and practical choice for transporting your roller skates and accessories.","

ROLL-LINE Skate Rolling Trolley

\nThe Roll-Line Skate Rolling Trolley is an essential accessory for skaters who need a reliable and convenient way to transport their gear. This trolley is meticulously designed to accommodate one pair of roller skates along with all the necessary accessories, making it a versatile and practical choice for skaters of all levels.

\nOne of the standout features of this trolley is its spacious interior. Despite its compact size, it offers ample room for skates and various accessories, ensuring that you can carry everything you need for your skating sessions. The trolley measures 22"" (59cm) tall, 13.5"" (34.5cm) wide, and 9"" (23cm) deep, providing sufficient space without being bulky. The lightweight construction makes it easy to handle and transport, reducing the strain on your arms and back.

\nThe Roll-Line Skate Rolling Trolley is designed with travel in mind. Its dimensions are perfect for fitting into cabin luggage compartments on most airlines, making it a convenient option for skaters who frequently travel for competitions or training. The trolley's robust wheels and sturdy handle ensure smooth and effortless mobility, allowing you to navigate through airports and other travel hubs with ease.

\nConstructed from high-quality materials, this trolley is built to last. It offers excellent protection for your skates and accessories, keeping them safe from damage during transport. The durable fabric and reinforced seams ensure that the trolley can withstand regular use and the rigors of travel. The interior is thoughtfully designed to secure your gear, preventing any movement or shifting that could cause damage.

\nThe Roll-Line Skate Rolling Trolley comes with several convenient features that enhance its usability. It includes multiple compartments and pockets for organizing your accessories, ensuring that everything has its place. The main compartment is spacious enough to hold a pair of skates, while additional pockets can store items like protective gear, tools, and personal belongings. The trolley's ergonomic design makes it easy to load and unload your gear, saving you time and effort.

\nChoosing the Roll-Line Skate Rolling Trolley means opting for convenience, durability, and style. This trolley not only meets the practical needs of skaters but also adds a touch of sophistication to your gear. Its sleek design and professional appearance make it a standout choice for skaters who value both functionality and aesthetics.

Skates U.S. Precision WHEEL HONING Tool 

Best used when:

- The Bearing Pocket is not exactly Squared or the sides of the wheel web that the Bearings press against are not exactly parallel. 
- The plastic Chrome or other surface materials do not allow for a perfectly square corner to the wheel hub causing misalignment of the Bearings and not allowing the wheel to roll freely.

There are large pass-throughs at each end of the tool in case there is a need to insert a breaker bar or screwdriver to allow more torque. 

There are also parallel flats on the non-cutting end of the tool to allow placement in a vice\, which will allow more torque on the Cutter end of the Precision Tool.

42440,simple,BontInlineJesaCeracBearing,,Bont Jesa 608 Ceramic Inline Skate Bearings,1,0,visible,The Bont Jesa Ceramic bearings are back and better than ever!,"
Bont Jesa 608 Ceramic Inline Skate Bearings

Bont and JESA have created the best inline speed skating bearing! JESA is one of Switzerland’s best speciality bearing manufacturers.

Bont Ceramics are lighter, with extended durability, and are more precisely round in comparison with the best steel ball bearings, giving you more speed.

Made in Switzerland, Bont ceramic bearings have incredibly precise balls and lightweight plastic cages, which produce less friction and drag. Ceramics are harder than steel bearings, this means they last longer with a reduced risk of bearing seizure, the ceramic balls generate less heat and offer considerable weight benefits. 

Invest in Bont Ceramics bearings today and go faster with less effort!

42447,simple,BontInline125skBearingprs,,Bont 125mm Inline Skate Bearing press,1,0,visible,The Bont Bearing Press is recommended for any skater who frequently changes bearings.,"<div>

\n
Bont 125mm Inline Skate Bearing press

\n

The Bont Bearing Press is recommended for any skater who frequently changes bearings.

\n

One end serves to press bearings into your skate wheels, while the opposite end allows for easy bearing removal!

\n

This inline bearing press can also be used for scooter wheels and roller skate wheels.

\n

We all know getting bearings in and out of wheels that use aluminum hubs is not easy, so Bont has developed a larger bearing press that is designed for 100mm, 110mm, and 125mm inline skate wheels.

\n

This skate bearing press makes it easy to insert and remove 608 and 688 bearings from your inline skate or scooter wheel.

Roll Line Action Adjustment Nuts for “NON-Click Action” (Set of 4)

Closest to the Skating surface

Variant M
Blaster

Roll-Line Adjustment “NON-Click-Action” Nuts or also called “Adjustment Nuts” are engineered to be light-weight and withstand the use and abuse of high level competitive Skating.

Roll-Line Adjustment “NON-Click-Action” Nuts or also called “Adjustment Nuts” are closest to the Skating Surface.  These specially designed Nuts have a NyLock insert to hold the Adjustment Position and are the same for ALL Roll-Line “NON-Click-Action” Skate Frames.

The back side surface of the “Adjustment Nut” actually fits into and goes through the Lower Suspension (Cushion) “NON-Click-Action” Cup.

Simply Adjust the Lower Suspension (Cushion) “NON-Click-Action” Nut or “Adjustment Nut”.   The “Adjustment Nut” adjusts the tension desired on the Suspensions (Cushions).
Left to Loosen
Right to Tighten
When looking from the bottom of the Skate Frame.
This adjustment is made with the 17mm end of the Tube Wrench.

If the Adjustment does not seem to stay as adjusted\, the Nylock insert in the “Adjustment Nut” may be worn out.  If so\, please replace the “Adjustment Nuts” to renew the settings and keep them.

It is suggested that if the Skate Frames are being used for several disiplines of Roller Figure Skating\, such as Figures (where fairly Tight Action is required) and Dance (where fairly Loose Action is required)\, that Skate Frames with “Click-Action” be employed.  The “Adjustment Nuts” with the Nylock Inserts WILL Wear out if adjusted on a regular basis.

Roll-Line Skate Frames (Variant M and Blaster) that originate with “NON-Click-Action” can be UPGRADED to “Click-Action”Systems\, by replacing the King Pin System and other parts\, which are included in the 13mm Ergal “Click-Action “04” King Pin Kit with Urethane Cushions.  

In most cases\, when setting up the Skate Tension Adjustments for the first time\, it is a good idea to loosen up the “Adjustment Nuts” all the way for all four (4) trucks.  This will allow you to count the “Turns or Rotations” and bring all four (4) trucks up to the same tension.  It is also recommended to make the Back Trucks (on each foot)\, be 1/8th ) turn Looser than the Front Trucks.  This will allow for easier steering when Skating Backwards.

If the “Adjustment Nut” is loosened to the point that it hits and is pushing on the Adjustment King Pin Locking Screw (the Keeper Screw)\, and more Action (flexibility) is desired in the Suspensions (Cushions)\, then a softer Suspension may be needed.

You should always used a spacer between your bearings to have a much better performance.

Why should we use Spacers in Roller Skate Wheels.
Any Wheel with Bearings\, when properly installed on Skate Axles\, should use Spacers.

If you look at the roller skating history years ago\, when we used Jam Nuts instead of the Nylon inserted Lock Nuts used today.
A Jam Nut must be locked down to keep from loosening and coming off.
To achieve good Roll from this type of configuration\, the sides of the spacer must be absolutely parallel\, without any burrs and just
a couple of thousandths of an inch wider than the web (that smaller center portion) of the wheel or space between the Bearings.
The sizes of the web of the Wheels vary between manufacturers and even between various wheels from the same manufacturer\, in some cases.

Many years ago\, the wheel manufacturers used to supply the Spacers with the Wheels.
When the Axle Nut is tightened down on the wheel (with bearings and a spacer)\, it creates a solid boss of material
(the inner race of the inside Bearing\, the Spacer\, and the inner race of the outside Bearing)
that effectively increases the Axle size from 7mm to approximately 14mm.
The increasing of the Axle size greatly reduces the possibility of bending or breaking any Axle.
By locking the Bearings and Spacer down\, it also assures that the center race of each Bearing is not spinning on the Axle\,
but that the balls of the Bearings are actually doing the work that they are intended to.
Tightening the Axle Nut on a Wheel without a Spacer can severely mis-align the center races of the bearings to the outer races
of the Bearings by compressing the inner races towards the center of the Wheel.
The Locked Down approach also requires near perfect alignment of the Wheel bore and the web of the Wheel must have very
clean square corners to provide a seat for the outer race of the Bearings.

Today\, Lock Nuts are accepted\, most Wheel manufacturers do not even supply the Wheel Spacers\, and the tolerances on the width
of the web of the Wheel are not held as tight as they once were.
To my knowledge\, Roll-Line is the only one still making Spacers for Wheels.
They normally come with a complete NEW Frame as an accessory.
Rollerskateusa.com does have spacers available in sets of 8 from Roll-Line.
(Just a Note: not every spacer will make every wheel work properly. Sometimes there are spacers that are non-parallel\,
have a burr\, or are just too small to match the web of a specific Wheel.)

The spacers have always been a part that the manufacturing cost must be minimized\, or for some manufacturers\, completely eliminated.
They are made from a long tube that is sawn into the Spacers\, and the tolerances are not usually as rigorously controlled as on other parts
of the Skate. To get the Spacers\, Bearings and Wheels to work\, means sometimes using multiple Spacers to get a specific wheel to roll properly.

When everything goes together well\, there should be little to no variation in the speed of a free spinning Wheel
(with the Axle Nut (Lock Nut) is just backed off) and when the Axle Nut (Lock Nut) is tightened down.

To achieve a Free Rolling complete set of Wheels in this manner will take time and patience and plenty of Spacers along with a good Bearing Press
like the our new Roll-Line Bearing Press/Puller.

All Roll-Line Wheels have either a Precision Machined Hub with the Tread adhered to it\, or
the Wheels are Molded with the Precision Center Hub type of configuration.

Roll-line Pivot Pin in Steel (Standard) 

How to Adjust the Pivot Pin

The Pivot Pin should be fully seated into the bottom of the Pivot Pin Cup.  There should be NO Side to Side (when twisting the Truck with your hands) or Up and Down movement of the Pivot Pin (when pushing straight down on the Truck over top of the Pivot Pin shank) in the Pivot Pin Cup.  

Be sure to NOT run the Pivot Pin Out too far or lengthen it to where the Pivot Pin is pushing on the Pivot Pin Cup and excerting pressure on the Suspensions (Cushions) and therefore the King Pin\, and actually changing the Angle of Action.  This is not a good thing.  The adjustment should be solid\, but do not over-do-it.

Once the Pivot Pin is in the correct position\, hold that position with the 7mm wrench.  Use a 13mm Wrench and tighten the Pivot Pin Jam Nuts against the shoulder on the Truck.  This needs to be as tight as is physically possible.  Lay the Skate on its side and actually lean on it and put your body weight into the tightening.  Remember to hold the Pivot Pin in the correct position with the 6mm wrench\, as it will tend to rotate with the tightening of the Pivot Pin Jam Nut.

The Pivot Pin is a hardened Steel and therefore much stronger than the Aluminum Truck internal threads that holds the Pivot Pin.  If the Pivot Pin is allowed to be loose (with the Pivot Pin Jam Nut not tightened)\, eventually the Pivot Pin will wallar out (or make open) the threads of the Aluminum Truck.  At this point\, no matter how tight you get the Pivot Pin Jam Nut\, it will NOT stay tight and will loosen up\, because of the openess of the threads in the Aluminum Truck.  The way to correct this issue is to replace the Truck with Axle assembly and make sure the Pivot Pins are adjusted properly and the Pivot Pin Jam Nuts are kept VERY tight.  Roll-Line recommends in their manual\, that the Pivot Pins be checked once a week.  I am sure there are Skaters that have never checked their Pivot Pin adjustments\, much less are\, checking them once a week. 

Movement of the Pivot Pin in the Pivot Pin Cup will wear out or destroy the high quality Delrin\, Pivot Pin Cup.  If these get torn up\, due to improperly adjusted Pivot Pins\, it is recommended that the Pivot Pin Cups be changed.

The Pivot Pin and it’s proper adjustment is VERY Important to the performance of your Roll-Line Skate.  So\, keep them adjusted or have your Skates maintained by a qualified Skate Technician.

The Pivot Pin is a hardened Steel and therefore much stronger than the Aluminum Truck internal threads that holds the Pivot Pin.  If the Pivot Pin is allowed to be loose (with the Pivot Pin Jam Nut not tightened), eventually the Pivot Pin will wallar out (or make open) the threads of the Aluminum Truck.  At this point, no matter how tight you get the Pivot Pin Jam Nut, it will NOT stay tight and will loosen up, because of the openess of the threads in the Aluminum Truck.  The way to correct this issue is to replace the Truck with Axle assembly and make sure the Pivot Pins are adjusted properly and the Pivot Pin Jam Nuts are kept VERY tight.  Roll-Line recommends in their manual, that the Pivot Pins be checked once a week.  I am sure there are Skaters that have never checked their Pivot Pin adjustments, much less are, checking them once a week.

How to Adjust the Pivot Pin

The Pivot Pin should be fully seated into the bottom of the Pivot Pin Cup.  There should be NO Side to Side (when twisting the Truck with your hands) or Up and Down movement of the Pivot Pin (when pushing straight down on the Truck over top of the Pivot Pin shank) in the Pivot Pin Cup.  

Be sure to NOT run the Pivot Pin Out too far or lengthen it to where the Pivot Pin is pushing on the Pivot Pin Cup and excerting pressure on the Suspensions (Cushions) and therefore the King Pin\, and actually changing the Angle of Action.  This is not a good thing.  The adjustment should be solid\, but do not over-do-it.

Once the Pivot Pin is in the correct position\, hold that position with the 7mm wrench.  Use a 13mm Wrench and tighten the Pivot Pin Jam Nuts against the shoulder on the Truck.  This needs to be as tight as is physically possible.  Lay the Skate on its side and actually lean on it and put your body weight into the tightening.  Remember to hold the Pivot Pin in the correct position with the 6mm wrench\, as it will tend to rotate with the tightening of the Pivot Pin Jam Nut.

The Pivot Pin is a hardened Steel and therefore much stronger than the Aluminum Truck internal threads that holds the Pivot Pin.  If the Pivot Pin is allowed to be loose (with the Pivot Pin Jam Nut not tightened)\, eventually the Pivot Pin will wallar out (or make open) the threads of the Aluminum Truck.  At this point\, no matter how tight you get the Pivot Pin Jam Nut\, it will NOT stay tight and will loosen up\, because of the openess of the threads in the Aluminum Truck.  The way to correct this issue is to replace the Truck with Axle assembly and make sure the Pivot Pins are adjusted properly and the Pivot Pin Jam Nuts are kept VERY tight.  Roll-Line recommends in their manual\, that the Pivot Pins be checked once a week.  I am sure there are Skaters that have never checked their Pivot Pin adjustments\, much less are\, checking them once a week. 

Movement of the Pivot Pin in the Pivot Pin Cup will wear out or destroy the high quality Delrin\, Pivot Pin Cup.  If these get torn up\, due to improperly adjusted Pivot Pins\, it is recommended that the Pivot Pin Cups be changed.

The Pivot Pin and it’s proper adjustment is VERY Important to the performance of your Roll-Line Skate.  So\, keep them adjusted or have your Skates maintained by a qualified Skate Technician.

How to Adjust the Pivot Pin

The Pivot Pin should be fully seated into the bottom of the Pivot Pin Cup.  There should be NO Side to Side (when twisting the Truck with your hands) or Up and Down movement of the Pivot Pin (when pushing straight down on the Truck over top of the Pivot Pin shank) in the Pivot Pin Cup.  

Be sure to NOT run the Pivot Pin Out too far or lengthen it to where the Pivot Pin is pushing on the Pivot Pin Cup and excerting pressure on the Suspensions (Cushions) and therefore the King Pin\, and actually changing the Angle of Action.  This is not a good thing.  The adjustment should be solid\, but do not over-do-it.

Once the Pivot Pin is in the correct position\, hold that position with the 7mm wrench.  Use a 13mm Wrench and tighten the Pivot Pin Jam Nuts against the shoulder on the Truck.  This needs to be as tight as is physically possible.  Lay the Skate on its side and actually lean on it and put your body weight into the tightening.  Remember to hold the Pivot Pin in the correct position with the 6mm wrench\, as it will tend to rotate with the tightening of the Pivot Pin Jam Nut.

The Pivot Pin is a hardened Steel and therefore much stronger than the Aluminum Truck internal threads that holds the Pivot Pin.  If the Pivot Pin is allowed to be loose (with the Pivot Pin Jam Nut not tightened)\, eventually the Pivot Pin will wallar out (or make open) the threads of the Aluminum Truck.  At this point\, no matter how tight you get the Pivot Pin Jam Nut\, it will NOT stay tight and will loosen up\, because of the openess of the threads in the Aluminum Truck.  The way to correct this issue is to replace the Truck with Axle assembly and make sure the Pivot Pins are adjusted properly and the Pivot Pin Jam Nuts are kept VERY tight.  Roll-Line recommends in their manual\, that the Pivot Pins be checked once a week.  I am sure there are Skaters that have never checked their Pivot Pin adjustments\, much less are\, checking them once a week. 

Movement of the Pivot Pin in the Pivot Pin Cup will wear out or destroy the high quality Delrin\, Pivot Pin Cup.  If these get torn up\, due to improperly adjusted Pivot Pins\, it is recommended that the Pivot Pin Cups be changed.

The Pivot Pin and it’s proper adjustment is VERY Important to the performance of your Roll-Line Skate.  So\, keep them adjusted or have your Skates maintained by a qualified Skate Technician.

The Pivot Pin and it’s proper adjustment is VERY Important to the performance of your Roll-Line Skate.  So, keep them adjusted or have your Skates maintained by a qualified Skate Technician.

Roll-Line Pivot Pin Cup

How to Adjust the Pivot Pin

The Pivot Pin should be fully seated into the bottom of the Pivot Pin Cup.  There should be NO Side to Side (when twisting the Truck with your hands) or Up and Down movement of the Pivot Pin (when pushing straight down on the Truck over top of the Pivot Pin shank) in the Pivot Pin Cup.  

Be sure to NOT run the Pivot Pin Out too far or lengthen it to where the Pivot Pin is pushing on the Pivot Pin Cup and excerting pressure on the Suspensions (Cushions) and therefore the King Pin\, and actually changing the Angle of Action.  This is not a good thing.  The adjustment should be solid\, but do not over-do-it.

Once the Pivot Pin is in the correct position\, hold that position with the 7mm wrench.  Use a 13mm Wrench and tighten the Pivot Pin Jam Nuts against the shoulder on the Truck.  This needs to be as tight as is physically possible.  Lay the Skate on its side and actually lean on it and put your body weight into the tightening.  Remember to hold the Pivot Pin in the correct position with the 6mm wrench\, as it will tend to rotate with the tightening of the Pivot Pin Jam Nut.

The Pivot Pin is a hardened Steel and therefore much stronger than the Aluminum Truck internal threads that holds the Pivot Pin.  If the Pivot Pin is allowed to be loose (with the Pivot Pin Jam Nut not tightened)\, eventually the Pivot Pin will wallar out (or make open) the threads of the Aluminum Truck.  At this point\, no matter how tight you get the Pivot Pin Jam Nut\, it will NOT stay tight and will loosen up\, because of the openess of the threads in the Aluminum Truck.  The way to correct this issue is to replace the Truck with Axle assembly and make sure the Pivot Pins are adjusted properly and the Pivot Pin Jam Nuts are kept VERY tight.  Roll-Line recommends in their manual\, that the Pivot Pins be checked once a week.  I am sure there are Skaters that have never checked their Pivot Pin adjustments\, much less are\, checking them once a week. 

Movement of the Pivot Pin in the Pivot Pin Cup will wear out or destroy the high quality Delrin\, Pivot Pin Cup.  If these get torn up\, due to improperly adjusted Pivot Pins\, it is recommended that the Pivot Pin Cups be changed.

The Pivot Pin and it’s proper adjustment is VERY Important to the performance of your Roll-Line Skate.  So\, keep them adjusted or have your Skates maintained by a qualified Skate Technician.

Roll-line 12mm Ergal “Click-Action” King Pin – Prior to “04”

Roll-Line 12mm Ergal Click-Action King Pins have a 13mm deep socket and thread that screw into a Roll-Line Skate Plate (labeled “04”\, which means the Skates were manufactured after 2004).  When installing\, a 16mm\, two (2) sided flat wrench will be required\, or better yet and the easiest way to change King Pins\, use the special custom Skates US King Pin Removal Tool.  The Skates US King Pin Removal Tool is usually mounted into a bench mounted vice or used with a large Breaker Bar.  Without the Skates US King Pin Removal Tool it is extremely difficult to remove the King Pin without damaging or destroying the wrench flats\, as the King Pins are installed with “BLUE” Removable Lock-Tite to ensure they stay locked into the Skate Plate.  When installing new King Pins ALWAYS use the “BLUE” Removable Lock-Tite.

Roll-Line 12mm Ergal Click-Action King Pins are engineered to bend before breaking\, so they rarely break. Normal causes for King Pins to need to be replaced are

1.  Mis-Adjusted Pivot Pins (see Pivot Pins for more information on properly adjusting) which move up and down or side to side in the socket\, allowing an extra ordinary amount of stress and strain on the King Pins.

2.  The Adjusting Threads on the bottom of the King Pin get Stripped.  This usually only happens when the King Pin Locking “Keeper” Screw is loosened and the Adjusting Click Nut is run on the very last thread or two.  (see Suspension “Cushion” information to ensure you are using the correct hardness Suspensions for your application.)

Roll-line 13mm Ergal “04” Click-Action King Pin 

Roll-Line 13mm Ergal Click-Action King Pins have a 13mm deep socket and thread that screw into a Roll-Line Skate Plate (labeled “04”\, which means the Skates were manufacturered after 2004).  When installing\, a 16mm\, two (2) sided flat wrench will be required\, or better yet and the easiest way to change King Pins\, use the special custom Skates US King Pin Removal Tool.  The Skates US King Pin Removal Tool is usually mounted into a bench mounted vice or used with a large Breaker Bar.  Without the Skates US King Pin Removal Tool it is extremely difficult to remove the King Pin without damaging or destroying the wrench flats\, as the King Pins are installed with “BLUE” Removable Lock-Tite to ensure they stay locked into the Skate Plate.  When installing new King Pins ALWAYS use the “BLUE” Removable Lock-Tite.

Roll-Line 13mm Ergal Click-Action King Pins are engineered to bend before breaking\, so they rarely break. Normal causes for King Pins to need to be replaced are

1.  Mis-Adjusted Pivot Pins (see Pivot Pins for more information on properly adjusting) which move up and down or side to side in the socket\, allowing an extra ordinary amount of stress and strain on the King Pins.

2.  The Adjusting Threads on the bottom of the King Pin get Stripped.  This usualy only happens when the King Pin Locking “Keeper” Screw is loosened and the Adjusting Click Nut is run on the very last thread or two.  (see Suspension “Cushion” information to ensure you are using the correct hardness Suspensions for your application.)

Roll-Line 13mm Ergal Click-Action “07” King Pin

Roll-Line 13mm Ergal Click-Action “07” King Pins have a 13mm deep socket and thread that screw into a Roll-Line Skate Plate (labeled “07”\, which means the Skates were manufactured after 2007 with the Lower Center of Gravity design or shorter King Pin).  When installing\, a 16mm\, two (2) sided flat wrench will be required\, or better yet and the easiest way to change King Pins\, use the special custom Skates US King Pin Removal Tool.  The Skates US King Pin Removal Tool is usually mounted into a bench mounted vice or used with a large Breaker Bar.  Without the Skates US King Pin Removal Tool it is extremely difficult to remove the King Pin without damaging or destroying the wrench flats\, as the King Pins are installed with “BLUE” Removable Lock-Tite to ensure they stay locked into the Skate Plate.  When installing new King Pins ALWAYS use the “BLUE” Removable Lock-Tite.

Roll-Line 13mm Ergal Click-Action “07” King Pins are engineered to bend before breaking\, so they rarely break. Normal causes for King Pins to need to be replaced are

1.  Mis-Adjusted Pivot Pins (see Pivot Pins for more information on properly adjusting) which move up and down or side to side in the socket\, allowing an extra ordinary amount of stress and strain on the King Pins.

2.  The Adjusting Threads on the bottom of the King Pin get Stripped.  This usually only happens when the King Pin Locking “Keeper” Screw is loosened and the Adjusting Click Nut is run on the very last thread or two.  (see Suspension “Cushion” information to ensure you are using the correct hardness Suspensions for your application.)

When using the Roll-Line 13mm Ergal Click-Action “07” King Pins\, the large (Upper Suspension (Cushion) will be smaller or slightly shorter than those used in the other models of Roll-Line Skate Frames.  In the “07” models\, the Suspensions (Cushions) will usually be one (1) level softer than used on other models of Roll-Line Skate Frames.

Roll-line 12mm Ergal “04” NON Click-Action King Pin 

Roll-Line 12mm Ergal NON-Click-Action King Pins have a 13mm deep socket and thread that screw into a Roll-Line Skate Plate (labeled “04”\, which means the Skates were manufactured after 2004).  When installing\, a 17mm Hex wrench will be required\, or better yet and the easiest way to change King Pins\, is to use the Tube Wrench\, mounted in a bench mounted Vice.  Without the Roll-Line Tube Wrench or a very deep 17mm socket it is extremely difficult to remove the King Pin without damaging or destroying it.  The King Pins are installed with “BLUE” Removable Lock-Tite to ensure they stay locked into the Skate Plate.  When installing new King Pins ALWAYS use the “BLUE” Removable Lock-Tite.

Roll-Line 12mm Ergal NON-Click-Action King Pins are engineered to bend before breaking\, so they rarely break. Normal causes for King Pins to need to be replaced are

1.  Mis-Adjusted Pivot Pins (see Pivot Pins for more information on properly adjusting) which move up and down or side to side in the socket\, allowing an extra ordinary amount of stress and strain on the King Pins.

2.  The Adjusting Threads on the bottom of the King Pin get Stripped.  This usually only happens when the King Pin Locking “Keeper” Screw is loosened and the Adjusting Nut is run on the very last thread or two.  (see Suspension “Cushion” information to ensure you are using the correct hardness Suspensions for your application.)

Roll-line Mounting Hardware (Fixing Kit)

The Mounting Hardware Kit (Fixing Kit) should be used with an 11/64? Drill Bit and a Countersink when drilling your Skating Boots. Please follow the instructions in the Learning Center at www.SkatesUS.com. The Mounting Slide Show will provide step by step instructions on the best way to mount Skates and Frames together. On Today’s Skating Boots\, it is strongly recommended to NOT use the Snyder Boot marking tool\, as this will in most cases move the Toe of the Frame too far to the outside of the boot.


It is strongly recommended to use all Four (4) of the Mounting Hardware Kit (Fixing Kit) Short Bolts\, Washers\, and Nuts and the EDEA Power Wedges in the Ball area of both Skating Boots\, if they do not have the NEW Planar Roller Sole. All Traditional Leather Skating Boots should utilize Power Wedges.  Be sure to tighten all of the Mounting Nuts and even consider using a touch of Blue\, Removable Lock Title.

Roll Line 4mm Allen L WRENCH Tool  

The Roll-Line 4mm Allen L WRENCH is used to Tighten the King Pin Locking Screw\, also called the “KEEPER Screw”.

Keeping the King Pin Locking Screw Tight is very important to the safety of the Skaters. The King Pin Locking Screw is also known as the “KEEPER Screw”\, as it keeps the Adjustment Nut from being able to be backed off to the point that the skate will come apart\, while skating. 

If the King Pin Action Adjustment Nut or Click Nuts are loosened (to achieve more flexible Action) to the point that they hit the “Keeper Screw”\, the Action has been Loosened to the maximum. This is based on the Suspensions (Cushions) that you are using. 

If you need more Action\, a more flexible Suspension (Cushion) will be required\, to allow the Skate Adjustment to be operated in the normal operating range of the adjustment. The Normal Operating Range\, Does NOT include backing out the “KEEPER Screw” to achieve a more Flexible Action.

The Toe Stop Allen Screw is another adjustment that was made with the 4mm Allen L Wrench. This applied some of the older (Prior to 2003) Roll-Line Frames. ALL newer frames use 5mm Toe Stop Allen Screws for this adjustment.

The Roll-Line 5mm Allen L WRENCH is used to Tighten the Toe Stop Allen Screw.

The Toe Stop Allen Screw should be kept tight\, but not Over Tightened. Once the Toe Stop will not turn and is locked in solidly\, stop tightening.

DO NOT Use an American 3/16ths Allen Wrench\, as this will strip out the Allen Screw head and make it very hard to tighten or loosen the Toe Stop Allen Screw.

The Toe Stop Allen Screw socket\, in the Frame (Plate)\, must be lubricated. Keep the threads and the socket that the rear of the Allen Screw head well lubricated with Lithium Grease (a medium weight white grease). Keeping these areas well lubricated will allow the Toe Stop to be easily Tightened and Loosened.

A trick that works on most Frames (Plates)\, to keep the Toe Stop TIGHT\, is to take the Toe Stop out\, make sure the Allen Screw is properly lubricated\, then Tighten the Allen Screw\, very tight\, leave it overnight. This draws the Frame together and makes it a tighter fit for the Toe Stop. Re-Install the Toe Stop and tighten appropriately\, but do not over-tighten the Allen Screw.

Roll Line 6mm Pivot Pin WRENCH Tool

The Pivot Pin Adjustment is one of the most often improperly adjusted parts of any Roller Skate with Adjustable Pivot Pins. 

The Pivot Pin a Ball and Socket Configuration. The Pivot Pin is the Ball and the socket in the Frame or Hanger is the Socket. 

The Pivot Pin should be firmly seated into the bottom of the Socket. 

There should be No Up and Down Movement or Side to Side Movement of the Pivot Pin in the Socket. 

The Pivot Pin should also Not be Over Extended\, as this will cause a severe mis-alignment of the Truck angles.

Once the Pivot Pin is in the proper position use the 6mm Wrench to hold the Pivot Pin in position and tighten (to the MAX) the Pivot Pin Jam Nut with the 13mm Wrench. It is recommended that the Pivot Pin adjustment be looked at or observed every time you skate\, and checked at least once a week\, if you skate frequently or skate hard. The Adjustable Pivot Pin provides greatly increased skate response and performance\, but an improperly adjusted Pivot Pin is the primary cause of broken King Pins and other skate malfunctions.

It is recommended to File the tip of the remaining protrusion of the Bolt, so it will not cut a misplaced finger. Filing also helps to ensure that the Mounting Nuts will not come loose.
42559,simple,SkateUSCstmKngPnRmvT,,Skate US Custom KING PIN REMOVAL TOOL,1,0,visible,The Custom KING PIN REMOVAL TOOL is used to remove and install King Pins from and into Roll-Line Frames.,"<div>

Skate US Custom KING PIN REMOVAL TOOL

\n
Skates US Custom KING PIN REMOVAL TOOL for Roll-Line Frames.
",,,taxable,,1,,,0,0,1.0,,,,1,,,50.0,"Roller Skates > Edea Roller Skate > Edea Accessories, Roller Skates > Roll Line Skates > Roll Line Tools",,,http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/customkingpinremovaltool.jpeg,,,,,SkateUSCstmKngPnRmvT,,,,0,Edea,,,ExtraField 1,Skate US Custom KING PIN REMOVAL TOOL,1.0,0.0,ExtraField 6,"
Skate US Custom KING PIN REMOVAL TOOL

Skates US developed this tool with the desire of being able to remove and install King Pins without damaging the King Pins\, as happens when standard wrenches are used and without damaging the Frames. 

The Skates US Custom KING PIN REMOVAL TOOL is designed to be mounted into a well secured bench Vise (the best method) or can be used with a Breaker Bar or Large Screw Driver (in case of emergency or if a proper Vise is not available). 

The King Pin is slipped into the Custom KING PIN REMOVAL TOOL making sure that the 16mm Flats on the King Pin are securely positioned into the Tool\, then rotate the entire Frame (Plate) Left to Loosen or Right to Tighten the King Pins. When removing the King Pins\, a large amount of force will probably be needed\, as the King Pins are installed with Removable Lock-Tite (Blue) to provide extra security and prevent the King Ping from loosening up when skated on. 

Please Note: ALWAYS use Removable Lock-Tite (Blue) when installing King Pins in Frames and make extra sure that the King Pins are Securely and Firmly seated and tightened into the Frames. Wipe away the excess Lock-Tite immediately when the King Pins have been installed.

The Roll-Line Precision Heavy Duty Bearing Press can be portable or mounted to a work bench for maximum stability. 

The following are a few suggestions on Bearing Care:


1. Bearings should never be handled with bare hands. Talc-free finger cots or talc-free surgical gloves should be worn.
2. Work areas must be clean\, clean\, clean (no food or smoking should be allowed)
3. be sure to clean the wheel housings and axle shafts thoroughly before installing or mounting wheels.
4. Be sure to use a Bearing press that will install the Bearings Squarely into the Wheels. Force should be only applied to the outer race when installing the Bearings into the Wheels. Force should not be applied to the Bearings in a manner such that force is transmitted from one bearing ring to the other ring through the balls.
5. Be EXTREMELY gentle when pulling Bearings from Wheels\, using the inner race. Rotate the wheel and bearing while extracting the Bearings. When pulling the Bearings\, there is a great chance to damage the Bearings. Please be Careful.

45095,simple,BontInlineJesaBlckBearing,,Bont Jesa 608 Black Series Skate Bearings,1,0,visible,The Bont Jesa 608 Black are the fastest steel skate bearing on the market!,"<div>

\n
Bont Jesa 608 Black Series Inline Skate Bearings

\n
Bont and JESA have created the best inline speed skating bearing! JESA is one of Switzerland’s best speciality bearing manufacturers.

\n

JESA bearings were made using aerospace-grade steel for the outer race, and also double-polished the outer and inner race to provide the least amount of friction possible.

\n

The balls go through a number of stages of polishing, far more than any standard ABEC 5, 7, or 9 bearings to make sure that they are as round as possible.

\n

Additionally, the lightweight plastic cages allow for lower rolling resistance. To help reduce drag, Jesa increased the radial clearance providing slightly fewer total contact ball patches. Finally, we use a special lightweight racing oil from Germany called Kluber oil to top the bearing off.

\n

The result is the fastest steel skate bearing on the market!

45112,simple,BontInline688miniAdapter,,Bont 688 Mini Inline Bearing Adapter,1,0,visible,The Bont bearing adapter fits over your 688 mini bearings so they can be used in a 608 wheel hub.,"<div>

\n
Bont 688 Mini Inline Bearing Adapter

\n

The 688 mini inline bearing adapter is made of aluminum. The bearing adapter fits over your 688 mini bearings so they can be used in a 608 wheel hub. You will need 1 adapter per bearing.
\nThere are two advantages to using mini bearings.

column2: • You create a much lighter setup as a 608 bearing weighs 12 grams compared to a mini bearing at 4 grams and an adapter at 1 gram
• Mini bearings spool up faster than regular 608 bearings

45293,variable,BontInlineSpeedCrono2SpCell,,Bont Crono 2 Inline Skate With Supercell Frame,1,0,visible,The Bont Crono 2 inline racing skate aims to limit the friction from the air while you are skating.,"<div>
\nBont Crono 2 Inline Skate
\nThe Crono 2 for inline was designed to slip through the air while still retaining the functionality of being able to adjust your frame.

\n

This inline skate is made to order and is not kept in stock!The Crono 2 is the world's first aerodynamic speed skate. Inline speed skaters can reach speeds of over 100km/h (60/mph) on downhills and pushing your skates through the air becomes more challenging the faster you go.

\n

Available in Metallic Silver/Super Yellow.

\n

Regarding all Bont boots or skates, in many cases they will be in stock in the warehouse in Florida, but they could also be in Asia.

\n

If Asia we could expect 2 to 4 weeks to be delivered, we will only find out after the order is placed, and we will let you know by email.

48839,simple,Bont167Roller7miniBearing,,Bont 167 Roller Skate 7mm Mini Bearings,1,0,visible,The Bont 167 quad mini roller skating bearing has an exceptionally fine polished bearing track surface and incredibly precise balls.,"<div>

\n
Bont 167 Roller Skate 7mm Mini Bearings

\n

The Bont 167 mini roller skate bearing is custom-made for Bont by Jesa Bearings of Switzerland. It has a 16mm outer diameter and a 7mm hole hence the number 167. Some skaters call this type of bearing a 7mm bearing. 7mm axles on quad roller skates are popular on high-end plates to save weight. Bont also saved a lot of weight with our mini bearing wheels such as the Royal Assassin and FX1 but there was no bearing in the world that could fit our needs so we designed the 167.

\n

The Bont 167 quad mini roller skating bearing has an exceptionally fine polished bearing track surface and incredibly precise balls. The lightweight plastic cages allow for lower rolling resistance. The extremely strong steel helps the bearing keep its shape when under load.

Bont 167/688 bearing adapters fit over your 167 mini bearings so that they can fit into 608 wheels. These bearing adapters allow you to use a mini bearing in a wheel that was made for a larger 608 bearing. The benefit of using a mini bearing and an adapter rather than a 608 bearing is that you can create a much lighter setup with better acceleration.

48882,simple,BONTWheelsFX1RollerSk8,,BONT FX1 Roller Skate Wheels,1,0,visible," The Bont FX1 is an ultra-lightweight, ultra-high-performance roller skate wheel at an amazingly low price. ","
BONT FX1 Roller Skate Wheels

The Bont FX1 is an ultra-lightweight, ultra-high-performance roller skate wheel at an amazingly low price. Super high rebound urethane combines with a unique mini bearing hub for fast acceleration and quick laterals.

The Bont FX1 wheel is great for roller derby or indoor rink skating. It is one of the only wheels on the market that uses the smaller 688 or 167 bearings rather than the traditional 608 skate bearing. This saves 12 grams per bearing and a whopping 192 grams (6.8oz) on a set of skates. That is a pretty huge weight-saving. Not only that but mini bearings also spool up faster than 608 bearings getting you up to speed sooner. 

Bont has a long history of roller skate wheel production and the FX1 is an excellent wheel that is suited for general skating or roller derby bouts. It could also be used for outdoor skating but it is not a dedicated outdoor roller skate wheel. This wheel can be used on all brands of skates if you are looking to buy these wheels to upgrade the wheels that came with your skates, they are a great choice. Try some today!

48885,simple,BONTWheelsBallisticRollerSk8,,BONT Ballistic Roller Skate Wheels,1,0,visible,"The Bont roller derby Ballistic is a great mid-level wheel that has great grip, roll and wear properties. Ultra-lightweight and ultra-high performance, for this price, you can't ask for a better wheel.","
BONT Ballistic Roller Skate Wheels

The Bont roller derby Ballistic is a great mid-level wheel that has great grip, roll and wear properties. Ultra-lightweight and ultra-high performance, for this price, you can't ask for a better wheel.

The Ballistic roller skate wheel is designed to be used in a rink for indoor skating but it can also be used for outdoor skating. This wheel would make a perfect roller derby fresh meat wheel. It uses a classic retro-style hub that fits 608 bearings and is well suited to work with Bont's ABEC 5 or ABEC 7 roller skate bearings. The graphic is also retro-styled and similar to what you would see in the 1970s. 

The Bont Ballistic roller skate wheel size is 60mm in diameter which is a standard roller skate wheel size. Skaters report that this roller skate wheel punches well above its weight and it could easily be used by elite roller derby skaters. 

This roller skate wheel has been tested by Bont's elite roller derby team skaters and is well-liked in the roller derby community. It is an affordable mid-level wheel that works well and has a good balance between roll and grip.

48949,simple,MoxiMixtapeBearings,,Moxi Mixtape Bearings,1,0,visible,"The Moxi Mixtape Bearings are two-toned 16-pack of 8mm bearings, made for quad roller skates and packaged into a real cassette case.","
Moxi Mixtape Bearings

\n

Moxi Mixtape Bearings are two-toned 16-pack of 8mm bearings, made for quad roller skates and packaged into a real cassette case.

\n

These bearings are lightweight and durable to withstand all types of skating including ramp skating, outdoor skating, rink, and even roller derby. The balls are lubricated in the thinnest high-speed oil designed for quad skaters who crave a faster, more durable, and smooth forever roll experience, requiring a fraction of the cleanings that greased ones do. Mixtape bearings are pre-spun before they are packaged so they require no break-in session.

\n

Comes in a package with 16 purple and teal friction-resistant covers.
